  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "But in point of fact I saw matter cease to be matter; it became something else that we have no name for - but I swear, it was no longer matter. Conversely, it was not just a physical medium for thoughts because for one thing (to repeat) it was no longer matter, no longer physical in the usual sense. So matter ceased to be matter. Okay, did mind cease to be mind? Yes. It turned into -\n\nAll I can think of is Pythagoras' special use of the term Kosmos_. \"The harmonious fitting together of the beaut",
